title: Bobbins For Lace Making, 18th–19th century
creditline: Gift of Mrs. C. H. Judkins
description: Of walnut and other wood, turned in a variety of patterns characteristic of the Midlands and Devonshire and weighted with jingled glass beads, buttons, and shells.
